title: Records to assess racism complainst against VMI

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

In regard to the statements made by Mr. Jeremiah Woos before the Education Committee of the Virginia General Assembly, I request the following records on former cadet Jeremiah Woods, VMI Class of ’27:

For any of these records, I agree that 1 Personal Identifiable Information will be properly redacted as may be required by law, so long as that redaction is properly noted.

1.	He stated: “I arrived at the VMI in the fall of 2023 on a full-ride scholarship.” – Provide the records for this scholarship, including sources of funding, any agreements, and the details on the scholarship itself 
2.	He stated: “I'm a black man, a former cadet leader, and a researcher of VMI's history.” 
a.	All records showing any leadership positions he held
b.	The period he held them.
c.	If removed from a leadership position, the reasons.
3.	He stated: “From the start, I faced racial targeting.”
a.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation. “A cadre member asked me whether my refusal to shave was an excuse because I am black. “
b.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation, “My white peers asked whether I'll be a field slave or a house slave.”
c.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation that his white peers “ asked if I would marry, kill, or have sex with George Floyd. When I said neither, they replied, they already killed George Floyd and no one cared, so it doesn't matter.”
d.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation. “When I spoke about the displacement of VMI's first black superintendent, threats escalated.”
e.	 All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation, as well as any social media posting to Jodel or other platforms, and responses from other cadets for his allegation. “One social media circulating among cadets. “All con. All con. President Trump has just passed the N-word, I'm going to effing kill you act. #Beadvised.” – I understand that Jodel is an anonymous application, but also understand cadets and VMI administrators have administrative access and that postings to social media are not protected under FERPA or the FOIA.
f.	Records of the RAT class trips to New Market from Mr. Woods Matriculation year to the present including any scripts, talking points or agendas for the trips and rosters for cadets attending in response to his allegation: “Each year, cadets are taken to the Battle of New Market and taught how Confederate troops who fought exemplify the highest level of the Brother RAT spirit while enslaved people who supported VMI are erased.” This is to include, without limitation, the specific record of the year(s) Mr. Woods attended the New Market event.
g.	Mr. Woods stated: “In 2021, VMI was required by law to establish a memorial and a scholarship. While VMI is the only institution of the five institutions named in the law, VMI has not yet established that memorial.” – Provide records of this requirement and the current status.
h.	Mr. Woods stated: “Jackson Hope board named after Stonewall Jackson.” – Provide the charter and results of the BOV review of monuments and namings report regarding the Jackson-Hope Medal.
i.	Mr. Woods stated on Social Media: “On 2025, I conducted historical research on enslaved African Americans who lived and worked at VMI, drawing from primary institutional sources. I presented this research publicly to a standing-room-only audience that included VMI officials and local elected leaders. My work demonstrated that enslaved people were essential to the daily operation of the institute, yet their lives remain largely absent from VMI’s Official commemorative landscape.” – It is my understanding this was a SURI project entitled “African Americans at VMI 1851 – 1865” under the VMI History Department. I request the record, including his research report with all underlying empirical information, his faculty and other advisors, reviews and drafts of his paper, correspondences regarding his paper and research, presentations, and attendance at the event he references.
j.	In his social media posts, he mentions building names after Confederate figures – I request a copy of the final monuments and memorials review report to the BOV and the BOV’s approval of said report.
k.	Mr. Woods identifies “confederate artillery” named “Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John” – records showing the confederate lineage of these weapons.
l.	Mr. Woods stated on social media: “Before ever speaking I met privately and repeatedly over the course of two years with Institute Officials across multiple administrations. I raised concerns about racial hostility, retaliation, and equity. These concerns were acknowledged, but meaningful change but did not follow.” – All records of these meetings especially with cadet leadership, Maj. Gen. Cedric Wins, Lt. Gen. Furness, the DEI/DOI/Inclusive excellence staffs or other Institute officials he met with.
m.	Mr. Wood stated “racist and threatening statements made by cadets on social media are real and documented.” – copies of these posts.
4.	Communications of any kind with Lt. Gen. David Furness, Maj. Gen. Cedric Wins, Col. Tinni Sen, Col. Keith Kline, or any member of the Title IX or DEO/DEI/Inclusive Excellence office from the date of his arrival at VMI to the present.

These allegations are a matter of great public interest and had significant impact of the General Assembly’s decision not move the bill to study if VMI should continue to receive state funding forward.  It is in the best interest of the public and VMI, especially its cadets, the facts of this matter are made public. To that end I request any fee for this FOIA be waived.

Further, in the past, VMI responded vaguely stating you could not locate some records.  In regard to the complaints Mr. Woods alleges he made should the search find no records I quest VMI clarify this by confirming “no record of any such complaint was found.”

It is in VMI’s best interest for the facts of this matter to be clear.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Anonymous.

Opera House Hotel, at 436 East 149th Street, Bronx, New York 100455; 5. Citywide cooling towers investigation; 6. Legionella DNA fingerprinting and results, pulse field gel electrophoresis (PFGE) testing, sequenced based typing (SBT), and whole genome sequencing (WGs) of environmental samples and human isolates; 7. Any patient reporting of Legionnaires’ Disease and/or related illness; 8. Any testing performed at the New York Public Health Laboratory and New York Wadsworth Center Laboratory;

title: George W. Bush Presidential Library: Records on U.S.-Estonian Coordination for Georgian Cyber Defense (August 2008)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting access to records maintained by the National Security Council (NSC) and the Office of the National Security Advisor created between August 8, 2008, and December 31, 2008.

Specifically, I am seeking records concerning the coordination between the United States, the Government of Estonia, and the Government of Georgia regarding the transfer, implementation, or advising of Cyber-Defense Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures (TTPs) during and immediately following the Russo-Georgian War.

Responsive records should include but not be limited to:

Diplomatic Cables and Memos: Communications between the White House and the U.S. Embassy in Tallinn regarding Estonian "Computer Emergency Response Team" (CERT-EE) deployments or technical assistance to Georgia.

NSC "Summaries of Conclusions": Records of meetings where the "cyber alliance" or technical cooperation between Estonia and Georgia was discussed, particularly concerning the mitigation of Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks attributed to the Russian Business Network (RBN) or other entities assumed to be formally or informally affiliated with the Russian state. 

Policy Guidance: Records related to the "provision of advice on cyber defense issues" as noted in the NATO-Georgia Commission framework established in late August 2008.

I request that the agency apply the "Foreseeable Harm" standard as codified in the FOIA Improvement Act of 2016. Given that these records are nearly 18 years old and concern a historical conflict involving a now-defunct criminal network (RBN), the disclosure of high-level policy coordination would not reasonably harm current national security. Please provide all reasonably segregable, non-exempt portions of responsive records, particularly those relating to public-facing diplomatic cooperation and general policy frameworks.

Keyword Search Appendix. Please conduct a categorical search for the following keywords:

Terms: "CERT-EE", "Estonian Informatics Centre", "Katrin Pärgmie", "Hillar Tork", "Cyber-Alliance", "TTP Transfer", "Tallinn Manual Precedents", "Information Blockade", "NATO-Georgia Commission".

Technical Identifiers: "AS40898", "BGP Hijacking", "Tbilisi Traffic Re-routing", "Tulip Systems coordination", "Tulix Systems coordination", "https://tulix.com/"

Section: Targeted Personnel and Offices

Please include in your search a categorical search for the records, calendars, and electronic communications of the following individuals and their respective staff during the August–September 2008 timeframe:

Melissa Hathaway: Senior Advisor to the Director of National Intelligence (DNI) and Director of the Joint Interagency Cyber Task Force. Hathaway was the primary architect of the CNCI and a key bridge between the intelligence community and the NSC.

Daniel Price: Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economic Affairs. Price was the lead on many G8 and international policy coordination issues during the Georgia crisis.

James Jeffrey: Deputy National Security Advisor. Jeffrey was heavily involved in the day-to-day management of the Georgia-Russia conflict.

Melanie Anne Gerber: Director for Cybersecurity on the National Security Council staff (2007–2009). She was a central node for interagency cyber policy.

Stephen Hadley: Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs (National Security Advisor).

Offices: The Directorate for Cybersecurity and Information Assurance and the Directorate for Central and Eastern European Affairs.

If certain parts of this request or certain portions must be redacted please provide any reasonable segregable portion of a requested record after removing or redacting those portions claimed to be exempt, explain in writing the justification for redacting the record, indicate the extent of any redactions on the portion of the record which is made available or published and where technically feasible indicate on the redacted portion itself the specific exemption(s) claimed.

Thank you for the George W. Bush Presidential Library's commitment to transparency.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Trevor Paul Moore (April 4, 1980 – August 7, 2021)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records mentioning, relating to, or generated as a result of investigation or inquiry into comedian Trevor Paul Moore (April 4, 1980 – August 7, 2021). His death is widely-known and widely reported; as such, privacy concerns under FOIA Exemptions 6 and 7 are voided, as are any concerns under the Privacy Act. For example, you may find his New York Times obituary at the following link: https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/arts/television/trevor-moore-dead.html

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records of both HQ and all field offices for all relevant names, agencies, organizations, companies and events including but not limited to those cited in the previous paragraphs and/or links as well as a cross-reference with the Southern Poverty Law Center to include any information provided by the SPLC. My request includes but is not limited to 137, 157, 176, 177, 183, 184, 188, and 214 files. If previously released records are available, then I request a rolling release consisting of those records while additional records are located and processed for release.

If any part of these documents are exempt from disclosure, please be sure to review and release all reasonably segregable nonexempt portions of responsive documents, as the FOIA requires.

I request that I be properly classified as a media requester. I am an assistant editor at Reason Magazine who has written numerous articles on topics of public interest, and I am requesting these documents in an editorial capacity. Please contact me if you have any questions about my media status.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Petti
